<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,978,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
The Afrotropical species 
<taxonomicName authority="Crass 1947" authorityName="Crass" authorityYear="1947" box="[906,1220,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Baetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvulus">
<emphasis box="[906,1083,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Baetis parvulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Crass, R. S." box="[1093,1220,979,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="37 - 100" refId="ref29311" refString="Crass, R. S. (1947) The May-flies (Ephemeroptera) of Natal and the Eastern Cape. Annals of the Natal Museum, 11 (1), 37 - 100." type="journal article" year="1947">Crass 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as male imagines from 
<collectingCounty box="[503,703,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">South Africa. The</collectingCounty>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Kopelke 1980" authorityName="Kopelke" authorityYear="1980" box="[799,1154,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Baetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="permultus">
<emphasis box="[799,988,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Baetis permultus</emphasis>
Kopelke 1980
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as male and female imagines (
<bibRefCitation author="Kopelke, J. - P." box="[489,662,1051,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="99 - 129" refId="ref31875" refString="Kopelke, J. - P. (1980 a) Ephemeroptera aus der Emergenz des zentralafrikanischen Bergbaches Kalengo (Zaire) Teil I: Baetidae. In: Entomologische Abhandlungen. 43 (6). Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde, Dresden, pp. 99 - 129. [1979]" type="book chapter" year="1980">Kopelke 1980a</bibRefCitation>
) and eggs (
<bibRefCitation author="Kopelke, J. - P." box="[791,966,1051,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="297 - 311" refId="ref31928" refString="Kopelke, J. - P. (1980 b) Morphologische Studien an den Eiern der Eintagsfliegen (Ephemeroptera) aus der Emergenz des zentralafrikanischen Bergbaches Kalengo. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaf, 53 (2 - 3), 297 - 311." type="journal article" year="1980">Kopelke 1980b</bibRefCitation>
) from Zaire (recently 
<collectorName box="[1215,1340,1051,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">DR Congo</collectorName>
). Larvae of the both species have not been described. Examination of larvae and winged stages associated by rearing from 
<collectingMunicipality box="[151,297,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">South Africa</collectingMunicipality>
and Tanzania suggest that they belong to one and the same species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
